LineNo: 15278135,

Narrator: It was late in the evening as I mad...
en


It was late in the evening as I made my way downstairs to discuss our reform plans.

LineNo: 15278333,

Manus Sazon: So, Your Majesty... Let's talk abo...
en


"So, Your Majesty... Let's talk about the contents of this reform, so that we could start drafting it with the RPP."

LineNo: 15278531,

Manus Sazon: I want to go over the main point o...
en


"I want to go over the main point of discussion to get a sense of your perspective and ideas first."

LineNo: 15278633,

Player_Romus: I have no problems with that.
en


"I have no problems with that."

LineNo: 15278735,

Player_Romus: I agree. The monarch should act as...
en


"I agree. The monarch should act as the head of state and not of the government."

LineNo: 15278837,

Manus Sazon: Our country still resembles an abs...
en


"Our country still resembles an absolute monarchy. Your father allowed the parliament to exist as a symbolic institution, and now we can give it the true authority it represents."

LineNo: 15278939,

Manus Sazon: After all, a constitutional monarc...
en


"After all, a constitutional monarch does not rule, Your Majesty, but they reign."

LineNo: 15279057,

Player_Romus: I disagree. Even with an empowered...
en


"I disagree. Even with an empowered parliament, the monarch should retain substantial powers over the government."

LineNo: 15279159,

Player_Romus: You are not thinking radically eno...
en


"You are not thinking radically enough, Mr. Sazon. I don't believe the monarch should reign at all."

LineNo: 15279261,

Manus Sazon: I know we had this conversation. B...
en


"I know we had this conversation. But I remain convinced that Rizia will not accept such a drastic change. Maybe someday."

LineNo: 15279363,

Manus Sazon: The constitution has to balance th...
en


"The constitution has to balance the power structure fairly so that no branch has complete authority over the other. That includes the monarch."

LineNo: 15279465,

Manus Sazon: That's what we've been campaigning...
en


"That's what we've been campaigning for."

LineNo: 15279567,

Manus Sazon: Firstly, the constitution will def...
en


"Firstly, the constitution will define the House of Delegates as the governing legislative body in Rizia. Their procedures and jurisdiction will be outlined clearly."

LineNo: 15279669,

Manus Sazon: Instead of the monarch, they will...
en


"Instead of the monarch, they will be in charge of managing the government budget and passing laws."

LineNo: 15279787,

Player_Romus: Only if their decisions are subjec...
en


"Only if their decisions are subject to the monarch's approval."

LineNo: 15279889,

Player_Romus: Only if the monarch holds the righ...
en


"Only if the monarch holds the right to veto their decisions."

LineNo: 15280183,

Manus Sazon: Hm... You can practice the act of...
en


"Hm... You can practice the act of royal assent to approve of legislature. But a procedure must be defined so that the monarch cannot block every single piece of legislature at his or her whim."

LineNo: 15280285,

Manus Sazon: Hm... We can implement a veto proc...
en


"Hm... We can implement a veto process. But it must be defined in a way that doesn't allow the monarch to block every single piece of legislature at his or her whim."

LineNo: 15280387,

Manus Sazon: Our main objective is to ensure th...
en


"Our main objective is to ensure the political participation of our citizens. This is only possible by limiting the monarch's power and enshrining it in the constitution."

LineNo: 15280489,

Manus Sazon: We can discuss the exact details l...
en


"We can discuss the exact details later."

LineNo: 15280591,

Manus Sazon: Secondly, we must decide whether t...
en


"Secondly, we must decide whether to keep the old regional structure in Rizia or centralize the system in Porte Drazon completely."

LineNo: 15280693,

Manus Sazon: Keeping the provinces semi-autonom...
en


"Keeping the provinces semi-autonomous is guaranteed to cause friction between the royal houses and the new government. But the nobles in those provinces have held power for centuries. They will not give it up easily."

LineNo: 15280811,

Player_Romus: I'd rather not disturb the regiona...
en


"I'd rather not disturb the regional system. We should respect the autonomy of the regions and make sure each is represented fairly."

LineNo: 15280913,

Player_Romus: Rizia still resembles a feudal sta...
en


"Rizia still resembles a feudal state. We should find ways to abolish that."

LineNo: 15281015,

Player_Romus: In a system that already has sever...
en


"In a system that already has several branches of government and many actors, a decentralized structure will only bring instability. I support centralization."

LineNo: 15281405,

Manus Sazon: I see.
en


"I see."

LineNo: 15281785,

Manus Sazon: A centralized government could mak...
en


"A centralized government could make things run more efficiently, but going against ancient regional traditions would be extremely disappointing for the authorities."

LineNo: 15281903,

Manus Sazon: Respecting regional traditions wou...
en


"Respecting regional traditions would be a clever choice. However, it raises questions regarding how the provinces should be structured in such a system."

LineNo: 15282021,

Player_Romus: The regions should have no autonom...
en


"The regions should have no autonomy or separate political structures. There must be equality among them and laws must be implemented in a uniform way nationwide."

LineNo: 15282123,

Player_Romus: While we should strive to achieve...
en


"While we should strive to achieve true representation among the regions, the nation of Rizia must be ruled by its parliament alone."

LineNo: 15282225,

Player_Romus: It might be unpopular, but this is...
en


"It might be unpopular, but this is what I believe."

LineNo: 15282327,

Player_Romus: Each region should function as a s...
en


"Each region should function as a state, and be allowed to exercise autonomy within the framework defined by the central government or the constitution."

LineNo: 15282429,

Player_Romus: We should respect the historical,...
en


"We should respect the historical, financial and demographical differences of the regions. Especially the Houses and the nobility. We need their collaboration if we want to change the system."

LineNo: 15282531,

Player_Romus: I wouldn't change anything drastic...
en


"I wouldn't change anything drastic. Keeping the current decentralized system will only increase public participation."

LineNo: 15282633,

Manus Sazon: We can offer the nobility somethin...
en


"We can offer the nobility something, I'm sure."

LineNo: 15282735,

Manus Sazon: I agree.
en


"I agree."

LineNo: 15282837,

Manus Sazon: I understand that, Your Majesty.
en


"I understand that, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15282939,

Narrator: He nodded.
en


He nodded.

LineNo: 15283041,

Narrator: He nodded.
en


He nodded.

LineNo: 15283143,

Manus Sazon: If the regions retain a degree of...
en


"If the regions retain a degree of autonomy, their local governments will share power and responsibility with the central one."

LineNo: 15283261,

Player_Romus: In a federal system such as this,...
en


"In a federal system such as this, having a second legislative body representing the provinces might be ideal. We could form an upper house."

LineNo: 15283363,

Player_Romus: We need to give something to the n...
en


"We need to give something to the nobility for their support. We could have an upper house composed of nobles who could provide some checks on the lower house."

LineNo: 15283465,

Player_Romus: The legislative body should be uni...
en


"The legislative body should be unicameral. Complicating the system will only make it less efficient."

LineNo: 15283567,

Manus Sazon: Abolishing the regional power stru...
en


"Abolishing the regional power structure would vest all powers in the hands of the central government. In a system such as this, I believe having a unicameral legislative body would be the best option."

LineNo: 15283685,

Player_Romus: I agree. Legislative responsibilit...
en


"I agree. Legislative responsibility must be solely left to one elected parliament."

LineNo: 15283787,

Player_Romus: Yes, we already have a parliament,...
en


"Yes, we already have a parliament, there is no need to create a second one and complicate the system further. This will only make it less efficient."

LineNo: 15284081,

Narrator: After I greeted Manus, I took him t...
en


After I greeted Manus, I took him to the wine cellars below the royal kitchen.

LineNo: 15284183,

Narrator: I flicked a switch hidden behind th...
en


I flicked a switch hidden behind the bottles. The shelf rotated to reveal an opening in the wall, which led to a series of wooden staircases.

LineNo: 15284285,

Narrator: I knew the perfect place in the pal...
en


I knew the perfect place in the palace to have this conversation.

LineNo: 15284387,

Narrator: I'd learned about this place from m...
en


I'd learned about this place from my father as a kid. It was a space that gave him the isolation he needed at times.

LineNo: 15284489,

Narrator: Contrasting with the immaculate int...
en


Contrasting with the immaculate interior of the palace, this part of palace seemed like it was abandoned.

LineNo: 15284591,

Manus Sazon: Your Majesty, this is a bold step....
en


"Your Majesty, this is a bold step. I cannot overemphasize how much I respect what you're trying to do."

LineNo: 15284693,

Manus Sazon: This will carve your name in the a...
en


"This will carve your name in the annals of history not as a monarch who clung to power, but as a visionary who saw beyond the crown."

LineNo: 15285003,

Manus Sazon: I understand where you're coming f...
en


"I understand where you're coming from."

LineNo: 15285105,

Manus Sazon: I see your point. You might be rig...
en


"I see your point. You might be right."

LineNo: 15285207,

Narrator: He took some notes on a small noteb...
en


He took some notes on a small notebook.

LineNo: 15285309,

Manus Sazon: The judiciary interprets, defends,...
en


"The judiciary interprets, defends, and applies the law in the name of the state -- and thus should be independent from other branches of government."

LineNo: 15285435,

Manus Sazon: And to ensure the constitution is...
en


"And to ensure the constitution is followed correctly, the judiciary must be given the right to cease executive and legislative actions that appears to be beyond their power according to the constitution."

LineNo: 15285537,

Player_Romus: I agree. Judicial independence ser...
en


"I agree. Judicial independence serves as a safeguard for the rights and privileges provided by the constitution. It should prevent the executive and legislative branches from encroaching upon those rights."

LineNo: 15285639,

Player_Romus: I agree. The effectiveness of the...
en


"I agree. The effectiveness of the law and the respect that people have for the law is dependent upon the judiciary's independence to make fair decisions. Politicizing it will only hurt the rule of law."

LineNo: 15285741,

Player_Romus: The judiciary can't be too indepen...
en


"The judiciary can't be too independent. There must be mechanisms to prevent their abuse of power. They can't lack accountability."

LineNo: 15285843,

Player_Romus: It is impossible to design a syste...
en


"It is impossible to design a system without any flaws. Judiciary is doomed to be politicized and it is in the best interests of the country to ensure that the executive and judiciary are politically aligned to prevent any feuds and government crises."

LineNo: 15286041,

Manus Sazon: Yes. The judiciary's role in decid...
en


"Yes. The judiciary's role in deciding the validity of the elections also necessitates their independence."

LineNo: 15286143,

Manus Sazon: I don't disagree entirely. But the...
en


"I don't disagree entirely. But the key is to achieve equilibrium between accountability and independence to ensure that justice is upheld."

LineNo: 15286245,

Narrator: He stopped for a moment to think an...
en


He stopped for a moment to think and went through his notes.

LineNo: 15286347,

Manus Sazon: I think we can make it work, Your...
en


"I think we can make it work, Your Majesty. The RPP can write a draft that we can all agree to."

LineNo: 15286449,

Manus Sazon: But the problem will be the forces...
en


"But the problem will be the forces against the democratic movement. The nobles, the police, the military..."

LineNo: 15286551,

Manus Sazon: We have to be careful while the co...
en


"We have to be careful while the constitution is being drafted. Nobody can intervene in the process until it's declared."

LineNo: 15287733,

Manus Sazon: I'll be honest with you. I am fear...
en


"I'll be honest with you. I am fearful that House Azaro has the power to contest this by deeming it illegitimate and executing a power grab."

LineNo: 15287835,

Narrator: His face turned extremely serious.
en


His face turned extremely serious.

LineNo: 15288215,

Manus Sazon: Tell me your honest opinion. Are t...
en


"Tell me your honest opinion. Are they a threat?"

LineNo: 15288365,

Manus Sazon: Many officers of the law, as well...
en


"Many officers of the law, as well as military personnel, are sympathetic -- if not outright loyal -- to Azaro family."

LineNo: 15288467,

Manus Sazon: Tell me your honest opinion. Now t...
en


"Tell me your honest opinion. Now that their attention and the bulk of their followers are in the war, do you think they can still pose a threat?"

LineNo: 15288609,

Player_Romus: I can't know for sure. General Tad...
en


"I can't know for sure. General Taddeus is in charge of the forces and I'm sure he's keeping his own forces safe and sound."

LineNo: 15288989,

Player_Romus: Actually, the bulk of their forces...
en


"Actually, the bulk of their forces were destroyed in the war. I don't think they have the capacity to strike."

LineNo: 15289639,

Player_Romus: Don't worry. I have total control...
en


"Don't worry. I have total control of the invasion and I will make sure their divisions are preoccupied or... sent to the frontlines."

LineNo: 15290019,

Player_Romus: We are losing the war, Manus. Thin...
en


"We are losing the war, Manus. Things are not looking good in the frontlines. But to answer your question, no, the military is far too preoccupied with the Palesian forces at the moment."

LineNo: 15290121,

Player_Romus: We are winning the war, Manus. If...
en


"We are winning the war, Manus. If we can't do it before the war is over, they will have both the means and their reputation as heroes to contest us."

LineNo: 15290223,

Player_Romus: I think we still have to be carefu...
en


"I think we still have to be careful. I don't think they will leave the frontline but Azaros are more than capable of a coup."

LineNo: 15290325,

Player_Romus: I don't think they are a threat. T...
en


"I don't think they are a threat. They can't simply go against both the will of the people and the monarch at the same time and expect to come out on top."

LineNo: 15290427,

Player_Romus: With Lucita in prison, their abili...
en


"With Lucita in prison, their ability to organize is weaker than before. But we have to be careful about her father."

LineNo: 15291085,

Manus Sazon: The intelligence and the police is...
en


"The intelligence and the police is behind our backs and watching our every step. This poses a great danger to our collaboration."

LineNo: 15291457,

Player_Romus: I gave the order to pull resources...
en


"I gave the order to pull resources away from suppressing your movement already. This should hopefully keep the police at bay."

LineNo: 15291559,

Player_Romus: I don't know, Manus... I've just d...
en


"I don't know, Manus... I've just disgraced General Azaro. I hope I didn't shoot myself in the foot there."

LineNo: 15291661,

Player_Romus: I've already done a lot on that fr...
en


"I've already done a lot on that front. Azaros are not in charge of the security forces anymore."

LineNo: 15292033,

Player_Romus: Ever since the removal of provinci...
en


"Ever since the removal of provincial levies, the threat they pose has been significantly less."

LineNo: 15292135,

Player_Romus: I can possibly try and handle Luci...
en


"I can possibly try and handle Lucita. She and I are very close."

LineNo: 15292237,

Player_Romus: They can definitely be a threat.
en


"They can definitely be a threat."

LineNo: 15292339,

Manus Sazon: If you can get her to support us -...
en


"If you can get her to support us -- then we'd be clear on that front."

LineNo: 15292441,

Manus Sazon: Yes, but they still hold significa...
en


"Yes, but they still hold significant sway in Montaklar and beyond. But you might be right about their threat being minimal."

LineNo: 15292543,

Manus Sazon: Thank you, Your Majesty. But this...
en


"Thank you, Your Majesty. But this will not stop their military faction."

LineNo: 15292645,

Manus Sazon: I agree.
en


"I agree."

LineNo: 15293017,

Player_Romus: I can possibly try and handle Luci...
en


"I can possibly try and handle Lucita. She and I are very close."

LineNo: 15293119,

Player_Romus: I'd rather be diplomatic with them...
en


"I'd rather be diplomatic with them. If we can offer the nobles a place in the upper house, we can potentially work with them."

LineNo: 15293499,

Player_Romus: I'd rather be diplomatic with them...
en


"I'd rather be diplomatic with them. Maybe instead of a unicameral parliament, we form an upper house made out of nobles, and compromise with them in exchange for their support."

LineNo: 15293601,

Manus Sazon: That's the problem.
en


"That's the problem."

LineNo: 15293703,

Manus Sazon: Hm. Perhaps we can.
en


"Hm. Perhaps we can."

LineNo: 15293805,

Manus Sazon: Interesting news...
en


"Interesting news..."

LineNo: 15293907,

Manus Sazon: An interesting plan...
en


"An interesting plan..."

LineNo: 15294009,

Manus Sazon: If you can get her to support us -...
en


"If you can get her to support us -- then we'd be clear on that front."

LineNo: 15294111,

Manus Sazon: I hope you are right.
en


"I hope you are right."

LineNo: 15294213,

Manus Sazon: I understand...
en


"I understand..."

LineNo: 15294315,

Manus Sazon: That might become a problem.
en


"That might become a problem."

LineNo: 15294417,

Manus Sazon: I see...
en


"I see..."

LineNo: 15294711,

Manus Sazon: We can offer to establish a 'House...
en


"We can offer to establish a 'House of Lords' that can provide a balance to the elected parliament. Including this in the draft might make them willing to have a dialogue."

LineNo: 15294909,

Manus Sazon: If you think they won't pose a thr...
en


"If you think they won't pose a threat -- then we are at least covered on that front."

LineNo: 15295107,

Manus Sazon: We have to either try to work with...
en


"We have to either try to work with them on this -- which means the constitution should reflect their will as well. This can be achieved by offering to establish a 'House of Lords' that can provide a balance to the elected parliament."

LineNo: 15295209,

Manus Sazon: We can include that in the draft a...
en


"We can include that in the draft as a compromise which might make them willing to enter a dialogue. Or we have to keep it secret and divert their attention away during the process."

LineNo: 15295589,

Manus Sazon: We have to either try to work with...
en


"We have to either try to work with them on this -- which means the constitution should reflect their will as well."

LineNo: 15295691,

Manus Sazon: This can be achieved by keeping th...
en


"This can be achieved by keeping the decentralized regional structure and offering to establish a 'House of Lords' that can provide a balance to the elected parliament. I don't think they would support anything that would take their regional power away."

LineNo: 15295793,

Manus Sazon: However, you also need to let of y...
en


"However, you also need to let of your plans of centralization. I doubt the Azaros will be open to have a dialogue if the constitution takes their regional power away."

LineNo: 15296173,

Manus Sazon: But even if that front is covered....
en


"But even if that front is covered..."

LineNo: 15296371,

Manus Sazon: But even if that front is covered....
en


"But even if that front is covered..."

LineNo: 15296473,

Manus Sazon: What about House Toras?
en


"What about House Toras?"

LineNo: 15296575,

Manus Sazon: Do you think your relatives can de...
en


"Do you think your relatives can decide to strike at the reforms? Your uncle holds incredible sway here."

LineNo: 15296701,

Player_Romus: We are not in best of terms with m...
en


"We are not in best of terms with my family. I don't think they will support the constitution in any way."

LineNo: 15297081,

Player_Romus: Don't worry. I have sway over my u...
en


"Don't worry. I have sway over my uncle as well. I think we can work with him if the regional structure and the nobility is respected in the draft."

LineNo: 15297183,

Player_Romus: If there is anyone who can claim t...
en


"If there is anyone who can claim the throne during a crisis, that's my uncle. I don't think I trust him."

LineNo: 15297285,

Player_Romus: Don't worry about the Toras family...
en


"Don't worry about the Toras family. They are not going to be a problem."

LineNo: 15297387,

Manus Sazon: That's a relief.
en


"That's a relief."

LineNo: 15297489,

Manus Sazon: What do you plan to do about that?
en


"What do you plan to do about that?"

LineNo: 15297607,

Player_Romus: If necessary, I will put the Golde...
en


"If necessary, I will put the Golden Guard around them and make sure they do not attempt to do anything until the transition is complete."

LineNo: 15297709,

Player_Romus: There is nothing we can do about i...
en


"There is nothing we can do about it. We don't need their support. They cannot simply fight against the democratic movement. Besides, I'm still the monarch."

LineNo: 15297811,

Player_Romus: We have to be diplomatic. My famil...
en


"We have to be diplomatic. My family needs to be involved in the reform discussions."

LineNo: 15297913,

Manus Sazon: I don't know about that... But I w...
en


"I don't know about that... But I want to trust you, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15298015,

Manus Sazon: Well...
en


"Well..."

LineNo: 15298117,

Manus Sazon: If you think that would really wor...
en


"If you think that would really work, Your Majesty..."

LineNo: 15298593,

Manus Sazon: And finally... There is Daria and...
en


"And finally... There is Daria and their national coalition. They still control the majority of the House."

LineNo: 15299251,

Manus Sazon: Although the unrest made them soft...
en


"Although the unrest made them soften up, we still need to make sure they support the constitution."

LineNo: 15299631,

Manus Sazon: There are also the demands of the...
en


"There are also the demands of the Wruhecist community who are backing the movement. You have to give something that makes them happy as well."

LineNo: 15299733,

Manus Sazon: There are also the demands of the...
en


"There are also the demands of the nationalists who are backing the movement. You have to give something that makes them happy as well."

LineNo: 15299835,

Manus Sazon: Otherwise, those people can turn a...
en


"Otherwise, those people can turn against the movement altogether."

LineNo: 15299953,

Manus Sazon: Otherwise, those people can turn a...
en


"Otherwise, those people can turn against the movement altogether."

LineNo: 15300071,

Manus Sazon: And finally... There is the whole...
en


"And finally... There is the whole task of uniting the House behind the constitution. But fortunately, I've got that covered."

LineNo: 15300173,

Manus Sazon: Any more thoughts before we decide...
en


"Any more thoughts before we decide on the draft?"

LineNo: 15300299,

Player_Romus: I WILL REVERT THE ROYAL DECREE
en


I WILL REVERT THE ROYAL DECREE

LineNo: 15300393,

Player_Romus: I WILL REVERT THE ROYAL DECREE
en


I WILL REVERT THE ROYAL DECREE

LineNo: 15300487,

Player_Romus: That will not happen. We cannot ma...
en


"That will not happen. We cannot make everyone happy."

LineNo: 15300589,

Player_Romus: I don't think they pose a threat....
en


"I don't think they pose a threat. What are they going to do after the constitution is accepted? If they go against it then, the justice system will take care of them."

LineNo: 15300691,

Manus Sazon: I don't know about that, Your Maje...
en


"I don't know about that, Your Majesty. But I'll trust your instincts."

LineNo: 15300793,

Narrator: He turned a page on his notebook an...
en


He turned a page on his notebook and looked at me.

LineNo: 15300895,

Manus Sazon: Uniting the house behind this powe...
en


"Uniting the house behind this power transition is essential."

LineNo: 15301013,

Player_Romus: Who will I appoint as head of gove...
en


"Who will I appoint as head of government until we can hold an election?"

LineNo: 15301115,

Player_Romus: If you couldn't even unite the par...
en


"If you couldn't even unite the parliament behind this, how will Rizia even recognize the constitution?"

LineNo: 15301217,

Manus Sazon: This would mean the head of govern...
en


"This would mean the head of government will be an elected official -- which can later be appointed by the head of state."

LineNo: 15301319,

Manus Sazon: They will lead a cabinet of minist...
en


"They will lead a cabinet of ministers, sit as a member of the House, and will be acting as the leader of Rizian government on behalf of the monarch."

LineNo: 15301421,

Player_Romus: I think you have way too many conc...
en


"I think you have way too many concerns, Manus. You should relax. I will take drastic actions, if need be. Any means are to be considered for democracy."

LineNo: 15301523,

Player_Romus: No. Let's start.
en


"No. Let's start."

LineNo: 15301895,

Player_Romus: Just be careful, Manus. I don't wa...
en


"Just be careful, Manus. I don't want anything to happen to you. If you hurt Vina, there will be consequences."

LineNo: 15301997,

Manus Sazon: Don't worry, Your Majesty. You can...
en


"Don't worry, Your Majesty. You can trust me."

LineNo: 15302115,

Manus Sazon: Well... I have no power to stop yo...
en


"Well... I have no power to stop you from doing that."

LineNo: 15302233,

Player_Romus: Let's continue with the draft.
en


"Let's continue with the draft."

LineNo: 15302335,

Manus Sazon: Alright.
en


"Alright."

LineNo: 15302437,

Player_Romus: She is there to represent and prot...
en


"She is there to represent and protect the rights of the nobility. How do you plan to get her to our side?"

LineNo: 15302539,

Player_Romus: The opposition and the monarch wor...
en


"The opposition and the monarch working together would be enough. Do we really need them?"

LineNo: 15302641,

Manus Sazon: Your Majesty, if the very institut...
en


"Your Majesty, if the very institution that you'll be empowering doesn't recognize or accept the transition, how would the constitution be put in place?"

LineNo: 15302743,
